WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.550 --> 00:00:05.558
Prof: So,
I've got to start by telling

00:00:05.558 --> 00:00:09.113
you the syllabus for this
term--not the detailed one,

00:00:09.113 --> 00:00:10.960
just the big game plan.
 

00:00:10.960 --> 00:00:14.772
The game plan is:
we will do electromagnetic

00:00:14.772 --> 00:00:15.570
theory.
 

00:00:15.570 --> 00:00:19.336
Electromagnetism is a new force
that I will introduce to you and

00:00:19.336 --> 00:00:21.070
go through all the details.
 

00:00:21.070 --> 00:00:24.863
And I will do optics,
and optics is part of

00:00:24.863 --> 00:00:26.580
electromagnetism.
 

00:00:26.580 --> 00:00:30.740
And then near the end we will
do quantum mechanics.

00:00:30.740 --> 00:00:34.710
Now, quantum mechanics is not
like a new force.

00:00:34.710 --> 00:00:36.490
It's a whole different ball
game.

00:00:36.490 --> 00:00:40.637
It's not about what forces are
acting on this or that object

00:00:40.637 --> 00:00:43.450
that make it move,
or change its path.

00:00:43.450 --> 00:00:46.316
The question there is:
should we be even thinking

00:00:46.316 --> 00:00:47.570
about trajectories?
 

00:00:47.570 --> 00:00:49.552
Should we be even thinking
about particles going on any

00:00:49.552 --> 00:00:50.030
trajectory?
 

00:00:50.030 --> 00:00:53.010
Forget about what the right
trajectory is.

00:00:53.010 --> 00:00:57.966
And you will find out that most
of the cherished ideas get

00:00:57.966 --> 00:00:59.010
destroyed.
 

00:00:59.010 --> 00:01:03.991
But the good news is that you
need quantum mechanics only to

00:01:03.991 --> 00:01:08.129
study very tiny things like
atoms or molecules.

00:01:08.129 --> 00:01:10.281
Of course the big question is,
you know, where do you draw the

00:01:10.281 --> 00:01:10.530
line?
 

00:01:10.530 --> 00:01:12.959
How small is small?
 

00:01:12.959 --> 00:01:15.998
Some people even ask me,
"Do you need quantum

00:01:15.998 --> 00:01:18.849
mechanics to describe the human
brain?"

00:01:18.849 --> 00:01:21.637
And the answer is,
"Yes, if it is small

00:01:21.637 --> 00:01:22.610
enough."
 

00:01:22.610 --> 00:01:25.289
So, I've gone to parties where
after a few minutes of talking

00:01:25.289 --> 00:01:29.058
to a person I'm thinking,
"Okay, this person's brain

00:01:29.058 --> 00:01:33.120
needs a fully quantum mechanical
treatment."

00:01:33.120 --> 00:01:36.638
But most of the time everything
macroscopic you can describe the

00:01:36.638 --> 00:01:39.709
way you do with Newtonian
mechanics, electrodynamics.

00:01:39.709 --> 00:01:42.569
You don't need quantum theory.
 

00:01:42.569 --> 00:01:46.796
All right, so now we'll start
with the brand new force of

00:01:46.796 --> 00:01:48.230
electromagnetism.
 

00:01:48.230 --> 00:01:51.705
But before doing the force,
I've got to remind you people

00:01:51.705 --> 00:01:55.242
of certain things I expect you
all to understand about the

00:01:55.242 --> 00:01:58.747
dynamics between force,
and mass, and acceleration that

00:01:58.747 --> 00:02:00.629
you must have learned last term.
 

00:02:00.629 --> 00:02:01.950
I don't want to take any
chances.

00:02:01.950 --> 00:02:10.982
I'm going to start by reminding
you how we use this famous

00:02:10.982 --> 00:02:14.310
equation of Newton.
 

00:02:14.310 --> 00:02:16.199
So you've seen this equation,
probably,

00:02:16.199 --> 00:02:18.913
in high school,
but it's a lot more subtle than

00:02:18.913 --> 00:02:21.307
you think,
certainly a lot more subtle

00:02:21.307 --> 00:02:23.720
than I thought when I first
learned it.

00:02:23.720 --> 00:02:27.491
So I will tell you what I
figured out over these years on

00:02:27.491 --> 00:02:30.318
different ways to look at F =
ma.

00:02:30.318 --> 00:02:33.324
In other words,
if you have the equation what's

00:02:33.324 --> 00:02:34.240
it good for?
 

00:02:34.240 --> 00:02:37.644
The only thing anybody knows
right away is a stands

00:02:37.644 --> 00:02:40.450
for acceleration,
and we all know how to measure

00:02:40.450 --> 00:02:40.870
it.
 

00:02:40.870 --> 00:02:44.400
By the way, anytime I write any
symbol on the board you should

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:46.889
be able to tell me how you'd
measure it,

00:02:46.889 --> 00:02:49.598
otherwise you don't know what
you're talking about as a

00:02:49.598 --> 00:02:50.199
physicist.
 

00:02:50.199 --> 00:02:53.102
Acceleration,
I think I won't spend too much

00:02:53.102 --> 00:02:55.060
time on how you measure it.
 

00:02:55.060 --> 00:02:57.610
You should know what
instruments you will need.

00:02:57.610 --> 00:03:00.921
So I will remind you that if
you have a meter stick,

00:03:00.921 --> 00:03:04.819
or many meter sticks and clocks
you can follow the body as it

00:03:04.819 --> 00:03:05.468
moves.
 

00:03:05.468 --> 00:03:08.454
You can find its position now,
its position later,

00:03:08.454 --> 00:03:10.830
take the difference,
divide by the time,

00:03:10.830 --> 00:03:12.110
you get velocity.
 

00:03:12.110 --> 00:03:15.143
Then find the velocity now,
find the velocity later,

00:03:15.143 --> 00:03:17.223
take the difference,
divide by time,

00:03:17.223 --> 00:03:18.889
you've got acceleration.
 

00:03:18.889 --> 00:03:22.639
So acceleration really requires
three measurements,

00:03:22.639 --> 00:03:25.532
two for each velocity,
but we talk of acceleration

00:03:25.532 --> 00:03:28.721
right now because you can make
those three measurements

00:03:28.721 --> 00:03:32.092
arbitrarily near each other,
and in the limit in which the

00:03:32.092 --> 00:03:34.988
time difference between them
goes to zero you can talk about

00:03:34.988 --> 00:03:37.590
the velocity right now and
acceleration right now.

00:03:37.590 --> 00:03:40.292
But in your car,
the needle points at 60 that's

00:03:40.292 --> 00:03:41.819
your velocity right now.
 

00:03:41.819 --> 00:03:43.750
It's an instantaneous quantity.
 

00:03:43.750 --> 00:03:45.870
And if you step on the gas you
feel this push.

00:03:45.870 --> 00:03:47.840
That's your acceleration right
now.

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:50.810
That's a property of that
instant.

00:03:50.810 --> 00:03:55.656
So we know acceleration,
but the question is can I use

00:03:55.656 --> 00:03:59.680
the equation to find the mass of
anything.

00:03:59.680 --> 00:04:03.078
Now, very often when I pose the
question the answer given is,

00:04:03.078 --> 00:04:05.513
you know, go to a scale,
a weighing machine,

00:04:05.513 --> 00:04:06.758
and find the mass.
 

00:04:06.758 --> 00:04:09.235
And as you know,
that's not the correct answer

00:04:09.235 --> 00:04:12.479
because the weight of an object
is related to being near the

00:04:12.479 --> 00:04:16.083
earth due to gravity,
but the mass of an object is

00:04:16.083 --> 00:04:17.480
defined anywhere.
 

00:04:17.480 --> 00:04:20.449
So here's one way you can do it.
 

00:04:20.449 --> 00:04:23.607
Now you might say, "Well,
take a known force and find the

00:04:23.607 --> 00:04:26.901
acceleration it produces,"
but we haven't talked about how

00:04:26.901 --> 00:04:28.550
to measure the force either.
 

00:04:28.550 --> 00:04:30.750
All you have is this equation.
 

00:04:30.750 --> 00:04:36.841
The correct thing to do is to
buy yourself a spring and go to

00:04:36.841 --> 00:04:43.338
the Bureau of Standards and tell
them to loan you a block of some

00:04:43.338 --> 00:04:45.759
material,
I forgot what it is.

00:04:45.759 --> 00:04:48.220
That's called a kilogram.
 

00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:51.060
That is a kilogram by
definition.

00:04:51.060 --> 00:04:53.009
There is no God-given way to
define mass.

00:04:53.009 --> 00:04:55.740
You pick a random entity and
say that's a kilogram.

00:04:55.740 --> 00:04:57.480
So that's not right and that's
not wrong.

00:04:57.480 --> 00:04:59.649
That's what a kilogram is.
 

00:04:59.649 --> 00:05:03.624
So you bring that kilogram,
you hook it up on the spring,

00:05:03.624 --> 00:05:07.456
and you pull it by some amount,
maybe to that position,

00:05:07.456 --> 00:05:09.088
and you release it.
 

00:05:09.088 --> 00:05:12.562
You notice the acceleration of
the 1 kilogram,

00:05:12.562 --> 00:05:15.649
and the mass of the thing is
just one.

00:05:15.649 --> 00:05:18.079
Then you detach that mass.
 

00:05:18.079 --> 00:05:21.807
Then you ask--Then the person
says, "What's the mass of

00:05:21.807 --> 00:05:23.259
something else?"
 

00:05:23.259 --> 00:05:25.149
I don't know what the something
else is.

00:05:25.149 --> 00:05:26.990
Let's say a potato.
 

00:05:26.990 --> 00:05:32.250
And you take the potato or
anything, elephant.

00:05:32.250 --> 00:05:33.750
Here's a potato.
 

00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:38.666
You pull that guy by the same
distance, and you release that,

00:05:38.666 --> 00:05:41.290
and you find its acceleration.
 

00:05:41.290 --> 00:05:44.581
Since you pulled it by the same
amount, the force is the same,

00:05:44.581 --> 00:05:45.500
whatever it is.
 

00:05:45.500 --> 00:05:47.889
We don't know what it is,
but it's the same.

00:05:47.889 --> 00:05:51.815
Therefore we know the
acceleration of 1 kilogram times

00:05:51.815 --> 00:05:55.369
1 kilogram is equal to the
unknown mass times the

00:05:55.369 --> 00:05:58.110
acceleration of the unknown
mass.

00:05:58.110 --> 00:06:03.860
That's how by measuring this
you can find what the mass is.

00:06:03.860 --> 00:06:05.939
In principle you can find the
mass of everything.

00:06:05.939 --> 00:06:11.141
So imagine masses of all
objects have been determined by

00:06:11.141 --> 00:06:12.560
this process.
 

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:17.226
Then you can also use F =
ma to find out what forces

00:06:17.226 --> 00:06:21.089
are acting on bodies in
different situations,

00:06:21.089 --> 00:06:23.783
because if you don't know what
force is acting on a body you

00:06:23.783 --> 00:06:24.970
cannot predict anything.
 

00:06:24.970 --> 00:06:27.581
So you can go back to the
spring and say,

00:06:27.581 --> 00:06:31.370
"I want to know what force
the spring exerts when it's

00:06:31.370 --> 00:06:33.329
pulled by various amounts.
 

00:06:33.329 --> 00:06:36.060
Well, you pull it by some
amount x.

00:06:36.060 --> 00:06:40.091
You attach it to a non-mass and
you find the acceleration,

00:06:40.091 --> 00:06:41.720
and that's the force.
 

00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:45.461
And if you plot it,
you'll find F as a

00:06:45.461 --> 00:06:50.392
function of x will be
roughly a straight line and it

00:06:50.392 --> 00:06:53.709
will take the form F =
-kx,

00:06:53.709 --> 00:06:56.199
and that k is called a
force constant.

00:06:56.199 --> 00:07:01.125
So this is an example of your
finding out the left hand side

00:07:01.125 --> 00:07:02.629
of Newton's law.
 

00:07:02.629 --> 00:07:06.567
You've got to understand the
distinction between F =

00:07:06.567 --> 00:07:08.610
-kx and F = ma.
 

00:07:08.610 --> 00:07:10.379
What's the difference?
 

00:07:10.379 --> 00:07:14.237
This says if you know the force
I can tell you the acceleration,

00:07:14.237 --> 00:07:17.910
but it's your job to go find
out every time what forces might

00:07:17.910 --> 00:07:19.379
be acting on a body.
 

00:07:19.379 --> 00:07:22.132
If it's connected to a spring,
and you pull the spring and it

00:07:22.132 --> 00:07:24.783
exerts a force,
someone's got to make this

00:07:24.783 --> 00:07:28.149
measurement to find out what the
force will be.

00:07:28.149 --> 00:07:31.519
All right, so that's one kind
of force.

00:07:31.519 --> 00:07:35.797
Another force that you can find
is if you're near the surface of

00:07:35.797 --> 00:07:38.446
the earth,
if you drop something,

00:07:38.446 --> 00:07:41.980
it seems to accelerate towards
the ground,

00:07:41.980 --> 00:07:48.079
and everything accelerates by
the same amount g.

00:07:48.079 --> 00:07:51.052
Well, according to Newton's
laws if anything is going to

00:07:51.052 --> 00:07:53.699
accelerate, it's because there's
a force on it.

00:07:53.699 --> 00:07:58.105
The force on any mass m
must be mg,

00:07:58.105 --> 00:08:03.519
because if I divide by m
I've got to get g.

00:08:03.519 --> 00:08:06.769
So the force on masses near the
earth is mg.

00:08:06.769 --> 00:08:09.750
That's another force.
 

00:08:09.750 --> 00:08:12.543
Something interesting about
that force is that unlike the

00:08:12.543 --> 00:08:15.240
spring force where the spring is
touching the mass,

00:08:15.240 --> 00:08:18.067
you can see it's pulling it,
or when I push this chair you

00:08:18.067 --> 00:08:22.250
can see I'm doing it,
the pull of gravity is a bit

00:08:22.250 --> 00:08:24.779
strange,
because there is no real

00:08:24.779 --> 00:08:28.250
contact between the earth and
the object that's falling.

00:08:28.250 --> 00:08:31.634
It was a great abstraction to
believe that things can reach

00:08:31.634 --> 00:08:34.610
out and pull things which are
not touching them,

00:08:34.610 --> 00:08:39.273
and gravity was the first
formally described force where

00:08:39.273 --> 00:08:40.629
that was true.
 

00:08:40.629 --> 00:08:46.168
And another excursion in the
same theme is if this object

00:08:46.168 --> 00:08:50.375
gets very far,
say like the moon over there,

00:08:50.375 --> 00:08:54.120
then the force is not given by
mg,

00:08:54.120 --> 00:09:01.519
but the force is given by this
law of gravitation.

00:09:01.519 --> 00:09:03.110
For every r near the
surface of the earth,

00:09:03.110 --> 00:09:06.386
if you put r equal to
the surface of the earth you

00:09:06.386 --> 00:09:09.428
will get a constant force that
is just mg,

00:09:09.428 --> 00:09:11.769
but if you move far from the
center of the earth you've got

00:09:11.769 --> 00:09:14.731
to take that into account,
and that's what Newton did and

00:09:14.731 --> 00:09:17.720
realized the force goes like 1
over r^(2).

00:09:17.720 --> 00:09:23.155
So every time things accelerate
you've got to find the reason,

00:09:23.155 --> 00:09:25.918
and that reason is the force.
 

00:09:25.918 --> 00:09:28.759
Many times many forces can be
acting on a body,

00:09:28.759 --> 00:09:30.952
and if you put all the forces
that are acting on a body and

00:09:30.952 --> 00:09:33.190
that explains the acceleration,
you're done,

00:09:33.190 --> 00:09:35.090
but sometimes it won't.
 

00:09:35.090 --> 00:09:38.428
That's when you have a new
force.

00:09:38.428 --> 00:09:42.710
And the final application of
F = ma is this one.

00:09:42.710 --> 00:09:46.102
If you knew the force,
for example,

00:09:46.102 --> 00:09:49.796
on a planet,
and here's a planet going

00:09:49.796 --> 00:09:53.190
around the sun and it is here.
 

00:09:53.190 --> 00:09:55.841
This is the sun,
and you know the force acting

00:09:55.841 --> 00:09:59.024
on it given by Newton's Law of
Gravity you can find the

00:09:59.024 --> 00:10:02.561
acceleration that will help you
find out where it will be one

00:10:02.561 --> 00:10:06.337
second later,
and you repeat the calculation,

00:10:06.337 --> 00:10:08.769
you will get the trajectory.
 

00:10:08.769 --> 00:10:10.558
So F = ma is good for
three things,

00:10:10.558 --> 00:10:13.730
that's what I want you to
understand: to define mass,

00:10:13.730 --> 00:10:17.413
to calculate forces acting on
bodies by seeing how they

00:10:17.413 --> 00:10:20.062
accelerate,
and finally to find the

00:10:20.062 --> 00:10:23.080
acceleration of bodies given the
forces.

00:10:23.080 --> 00:10:27.000
This is the cycle of Newtonian
dynamics.

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:32.215
And what I'm going to do now is
to add one more new force,

00:10:32.215 --> 00:10:37.705
because I'm going to find out
that there is another force not

00:10:37.705 --> 00:10:39.168
listed here.
 

00:10:39.168 --> 00:10:42.692
I'm going to demonstrate to you
that new force,

00:10:42.692 --> 00:10:43.230
okay?
 

00:10:43.230 --> 00:10:44.990
Here's my demonstration.
 

00:10:44.990 --> 00:10:48.750
The only demonstration you will
see in my class,

00:10:48.750 --> 00:10:52.830
because everything else I've
tried generally failed,

00:10:52.830 --> 00:10:55.230
but this one always works.
 

00:10:55.230 --> 00:11:01.149
So, I have here a piece of
paper, okay?

00:11:01.149 --> 00:11:05.619
Then I take this trusty comb
and I comb the part of my head

00:11:05.619 --> 00:11:08.470
that's suited for this
experiment,

00:11:08.470 --> 00:11:13.893
then I bring it next to this,
and you see I'm able to lift

00:11:13.893 --> 00:11:14.558
that.
 

00:11:14.558 --> 00:11:18.116
Now, that's not the force of
gravity because gravity doesn't

00:11:18.116 --> 00:11:20.649
care if you comb your hair or
not, okay?

00:11:20.649 --> 00:11:25.600
And also when I shake it,
it falls down.

00:11:25.600 --> 00:11:28.655
So you're thinking, "Okay,
maybe there is a new force but

00:11:28.655 --> 00:11:32.227
it doesn't look awfully strong
because it's not able to even

00:11:32.227 --> 00:11:35.514
overcome gravity,
because it eventually yielded

00:11:35.514 --> 00:11:39.754
to gravity and fell down,"
but it's actually a mistake to

00:11:39.754 --> 00:11:40.590
think so.
 

00:11:40.590 --> 00:11:45.880
In fact this new force that I'm
talking about is 10 to the power

00:11:45.880 --> 00:11:49.408
of 40 stronger than
gravitational force.

00:11:49.408 --> 00:11:52.950
I will tell you by what metric
I came up with that number,

00:11:52.950 --> 00:11:55.308
but it's an enormously strong
force.

00:11:55.308 --> 00:11:59.736
You've got to understand why I
say it is such a strong force

00:11:59.736 --> 00:12:03.038
when, when I shook it the thing
fell down.

00:12:03.038 --> 00:12:08.548
So the reason is that if you
look at this experiment,

00:12:08.548 --> 00:12:11.149
here's the comb and here's the
paper,

00:12:11.149 --> 00:12:13.070
the comb is trying to pull the
paper,

00:12:13.070 --> 00:12:17.259
but what is trying to pull it
down?

00:12:17.259 --> 00:12:21.220
What is trying to pull it down?
 

00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:24.337
So here is me,
here is that comb,

00:12:24.337 --> 00:12:26.190
here's the paper.
 

00:12:26.190 --> 00:12:34.260
The entire planet is pulling it
down: Himalayas pulling it down,

00:12:34.260 --> 00:12:38.104
Pacific Ocean,
pulling it down,

00:12:38.104 --> 00:12:44.509
Bin Laden sitting in his cave
pulling it down.

00:12:44.509 --> 00:12:47.220
Everything is pulling it down,
okay?

00:12:47.220 --> 00:12:50.729
I am one of these people
generally convinced the world is

00:12:50.729 --> 00:12:53.548
acting against me,
but this time I'm right.

00:12:53.548 --> 00:12:57.354
Everything is acting against
me, and I'm able to triumph

00:12:57.354 --> 00:13:00.259
against all of that with this
tiny comb.

00:13:00.259 --> 00:13:03.166
And that is how you compare the
electric force with the

00:13:03.166 --> 00:13:04.350
gravitational force.
 

00:13:04.350 --> 00:13:08.236
It takes the entire planet to
compensate whatever tiny force I

00:13:08.236 --> 00:13:11.360
create between the comb and the
piece of paper.

00:13:11.360 --> 00:13:13.582
To really get a number out of
this I'll have to do a little

00:13:13.582 --> 00:13:17.163
more,
but I just want to point out to

00:13:17.163 --> 00:13:23.080
you this is a new force much
stronger than gravitation.

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:27.102
So I want to tell you a few
other experiments people did

00:13:27.102 --> 00:13:31.200
without going into what the
explanation is right now,

00:13:31.200 --> 00:13:35.590
but let me just tell you if you
go through history what all did

00:13:35.590 --> 00:13:36.440
people do.
 

00:13:36.440 --> 00:13:42.678
So one experiment you can do:
You take a piece of glass and

00:13:42.678 --> 00:13:49.240
you rub it on some animal that's
passing by, water buffalo.

00:13:49.240 --> 00:13:52.580
That's why I cannot do all the
experiments in class.

00:13:52.580 --> 00:13:56.456
You rub it on that guy,
then you do it to a second

00:13:56.456 --> 00:13:59.467
piece of glass,
and you find out that they

00:13:59.467 --> 00:14:02.366
repel each other,
meaning if you put them next to

00:14:02.366 --> 00:14:04.330
each other they tend to fly
apart.

00:14:04.330 --> 00:14:09.264
Then you take a piece of hard
rubber and you rub that on

00:14:09.264 --> 00:14:10.788
something else.
 

00:14:10.788 --> 00:14:14.899
I forgot what,
silk, Yeti, some other thing.

00:14:14.899 --> 00:14:15.769
Then you put that here.
 

00:14:15.769 --> 00:14:18.669
So I'll give a different shape
to that thing.

00:14:18.669 --> 00:14:20.129
That's the rubber stick.
 

00:14:20.129 --> 00:14:25.335
And you find when you do that
to this, these two attract each

00:14:25.335 --> 00:14:26.028
other.
 

00:14:26.028 --> 00:14:30.139
Sometimes they repel,
sometimes they attract.

00:14:30.139 --> 00:14:35.048
Here's another thing you can
do: Buy some nylon thread.

00:14:35.048 --> 00:14:39.166
You hang a small metallic
sphere, and you bring one of

00:14:39.166 --> 00:14:41.029
these rods next to it.
 

00:14:41.029 --> 00:14:42.908
It doesn't matter which one.
 

00:14:42.908 --> 00:14:48.388
Initially they're attracted and
suddenly when you touch it and

00:14:48.388 --> 00:14:51.890
you remove it,
they start repelling each

00:14:51.890 --> 00:14:52.789
other.
 

00:14:52.789 --> 00:14:53.690
What's going on?
 

00:14:53.690 --> 00:14:56.149
That's another thing you could
do.

00:14:56.149 --> 00:15:01.389
Last thing I want to mention is
if you took two of these things

00:15:01.389 --> 00:15:05.110
which are repelling each other,
let's say.

00:15:05.110 --> 00:15:08.528
Let's say they're attracting
each other like this.

00:15:08.528 --> 00:15:12.871
Then you connect them with a
piece of nylon and you take it

00:15:12.871 --> 00:15:14.668
away, nothing happens.
 

00:15:14.668 --> 00:15:19.109
If you connect them with a
piece of wire and take away the

00:15:19.109 --> 00:15:22.379
wire, they no longer attract
each other.

00:15:22.379 --> 00:15:24.158
So these are examples of
different things.

00:15:24.158 --> 00:15:26.018
I'm just going to say,
you do this,

00:15:26.018 --> 00:15:27.330
you do this,
you do that,

00:15:27.330 --> 00:15:30.610
then finally you need a theory
that explains everything.

00:15:30.610 --> 00:15:34.308
So that's the theory that I'm
going to give you now.

00:15:34.308 --> 00:15:36.808
That's the theory of
electrostatics.

00:15:36.808 --> 00:15:40.335
And I don't have time to go
into the entire history of how

00:15:40.335 --> 00:15:42.808
people arrived at this final
formula,

00:15:42.808 --> 00:15:48.773
so I'm just going to tell you
one formula that really will

00:15:48.773 --> 00:15:53.899
explain everything that I've
described so far,

00:15:53.899 --> 00:16:00.009
and that formula is called
Coulomb's Law.

00:16:00.009 --> 00:16:02.727
Even though Mr. Coulomb's
name is on it,

00:16:02.727 --> 00:16:06.908
he was not the first one to
formulate parts of the law,

00:16:06.908 --> 00:16:10.990
but he gave the final and
direct verification of Coulomb's

00:16:10.990 --> 00:16:14.139
Law that other people who had
contributed.

00:16:14.139 --> 00:16:20.590
So Coulomb's Law says that
certain entities have a property

00:16:20.590 --> 00:16:22.370
called charge.
 

00:16:22.370 --> 00:16:26.767
You have charge or you don't
have charge, but if you have

00:16:26.767 --> 00:16:31.163
charge the charge that you have,
you meaning any of these

00:16:31.163 --> 00:16:34.070
objects, is measured in
coulombs.

00:16:34.070 --> 00:16:36.469
Remember, that was not
Coulomb's idea to call it

00:16:36.469 --> 00:16:36.980
coulomb.
 

00:16:36.980 --> 00:16:39.436
Whenever you make a discovery,
you're breathlessly waiting

00:16:39.436 --> 00:16:41.158
that somebody will name it after
you,

00:16:41.158 --> 00:16:44.330
but it's not in good taste to
name to after yourself,

00:16:44.330 --> 00:16:46.149
but it carries Coulomb's name.
 

00:16:46.149 --> 00:16:48.774
So he didn't say call it
coulomb, okay,

00:16:48.774 --> 00:16:51.470
but he certainly wrote down
this law.

00:16:51.470 --> 00:16:55.515
The law says that if you've got
one entity which has some amount

00:16:55.515 --> 00:16:58.149
of charge called
q_1,

00:16:58.149 --> 00:17:01.408
and there's another entity that
has some amount of charge

00:17:01.408 --> 00:17:04.726
q_2 they will
exert a force on each other

00:17:04.726 --> 00:17:06.704
which is given by
q_1q

00:17:06.704 --> 00:17:09.731
_2 times this
constant which is somehow

00:17:09.731 --> 00:17:11.711
written as 1 over
4Πε

00:17:11.711 --> 00:17:13.690
_0.
 

00:17:13.690 --> 00:17:17.009
That's 1 over r^(2).
 

00:17:17.009 --> 00:17:18.887
But r is the distance
between them,

00:17:18.887 --> 00:17:21.223
and you can ask in this
picture, what do you mean by

00:17:21.223 --> 00:17:21.818
distance?
 

00:17:21.818 --> 00:17:24.525
I mean, is it from here to
there, or is it from center to

00:17:24.525 --> 00:17:24.960
center?
 

00:17:24.960 --> 00:17:28.837
We're assuming here that the
distance between them is much

00:17:28.837 --> 00:17:31.220
bigger than the individual
sizes.

00:17:31.220 --> 00:17:33.422
For example,
you say, how far am I from Los

00:17:33.422 --> 00:17:34.786
Angeles, well,
3,225 miles,

00:17:34.786 --> 00:17:37.880
but you can say are you taking
about your right hand or your

00:17:37.880 --> 00:17:38.720
left hand?
 

00:17:38.720 --> 00:17:41.873
Well, I'm a point particle for
this purpose so it doesn't

00:17:41.873 --> 00:17:42.380
matter.
 

00:17:42.380 --> 00:17:45.585
So here we're assuming that
either they're mathematically

00:17:45.585 --> 00:17:48.961
point charges or they're real
charges with a finite size but

00:17:48.961 --> 00:17:52.108
separated by a distance much
bigger than the size,

00:17:52.108 --> 00:17:53.990
so r could stand,
if you like,

00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:55.549
for center to center.
 

00:17:55.549 --> 00:17:58.630
It doesn't matter too much.
 

00:17:58.630 --> 00:18:00.930
So this is what Coulomb said.
 

00:18:00.930 --> 00:18:03.058
Now, if you look at this number
here,

00:18:03.058 --> 00:18:05.858
1 over 4Πε
_0,

00:18:05.858 --> 00:18:12.009
its value is 9 times 10 to the
9^(th).

00:18:12.009 --> 00:18:16.307
What that means is the
following: If you take one body

00:18:16.307 --> 00:18:20.653
with 1 coulomb of charge,
another body with 1 coulomb of

00:18:20.653 --> 00:18:23.558
charge and they're separated by
1 meter,

00:18:23.558 --> 00:18:27.259
then the force between them
will be this number,

00:18:27.259 --> 00:18:28.880
because everything else is a 1.
 

00:18:28.880 --> 00:18:32.440
It'll be 9 times 10 to the 9
newtons.

00:18:32.440 --> 00:18:34.998
That's an enormous force,
and normally you don't run into

00:18:34.998 --> 00:18:37.507
1 coulomb of charge,
but the reason why a coulomb

00:18:37.507 --> 00:18:40.732
was picked is sort of historical
and it has to do with currents

00:18:40.732 --> 00:18:41.410
and so on.
 

00:18:41.410 --> 00:18:45.048
But anyway, this is the
definition.

00:18:45.048 --> 00:18:49.170
But if you want to be more
precise, I should write a

00:18:49.170 --> 00:18:53.288
formula more carefully because
force is a vector.

00:18:53.288 --> 00:18:58.118
Also I should say force on whom
and due to what.

00:18:58.118 --> 00:19:01.358
So let's say there are two
charges,

00:19:01.358 --> 00:19:05.339
and say q_1 is
sitting at the origin and

00:19:05.339 --> 00:19:09.817
q_2 is sitting
at a point whose position is the

00:19:09.817 --> 00:19:11.240
vector r.
 

00:19:11.240 --> 00:19:17.336
Then the force on 2 due to 1 is
given by q_2q

00:19:17.336 --> 00:19:22.790
_1 over
4Πε_0

00:19:22.790 --> 00:19:27.068
times 1 over
r^(2).

00:19:27.068 --> 00:19:30.281
That's the magnitude of the
force, but I want to suggest

00:19:30.281 --> 00:19:33.436
that the force is such that
q_1 pushes

00:19:33.436 --> 00:19:35.190
q_2 away.
 

00:19:35.190 --> 00:19:38.127
So I want to make this into a
vector, but I've got the

00:19:38.127 --> 00:19:39.568
magnitude of the vector.
 

00:19:39.568 --> 00:19:42.580
As you know,
to make a real vector you take

00:19:42.580 --> 00:19:47.096
its magnitude and multiply it by
a vector of unit length in that

00:19:47.096 --> 00:19:48.460
same direction.
 

00:19:48.460 --> 00:19:51.150
The unit vector we can write in
many ways.

00:19:51.150 --> 00:19:53.286
One is just to say
e_r,

00:19:53.286 --> 00:19:56.654
e_r_
is a standard name for a

00:19:56.654 --> 00:19:59.779
vector of length 1 in the
direction of r.

00:19:59.779 --> 00:20:01.298
But I'll give you another
choice.

00:20:01.298 --> 00:20:04.483
You can also write it as
r divided by the length

00:20:04.483 --> 00:20:05.308
of r.
 

00:20:05.308 --> 00:20:08.058
That also would be a vector of
unit length parallel to

00:20:08.058 --> 00:20:08.630
r.
 

00:20:08.630 --> 00:20:11.799
So there are many ways to write
the thing that makes it a

00:20:11.799 --> 00:20:12.308
vector.
 

00:20:12.308 --> 00:20:24.269
And F_21 is
minus of F_12.

00:20:24.269 --> 00:20:28.990
Now, how do we get attraction
and how do we get repulsion?

00:20:28.990 --> 00:20:30.300
We get it because
q_1 and

00:20:30.300 --> 00:20:32.509
q_2,
if they're both positive and

00:20:32.509 --> 00:20:35.665
you if you use the formula,
you'll find they repel each

00:20:35.665 --> 00:20:38.259
other, but if they're of
opposite signs,

00:20:38.259 --> 00:20:40.830
you'll do the same calculation,
but you'll put a minus sign in

00:20:40.830 --> 00:20:41.970
front of the whole thing.
 

00:20:41.970 --> 00:20:46.670
That'll turn repulsion into an
attraction.

00:20:46.670 --> 00:20:50.105
So you must allow for the
possibility that q can be

00:20:50.105 --> 00:20:53.048
of either sign;
q can also be 0.

00:20:53.048 --> 00:20:55.942
There are certain entities
which don't have any electric

00:20:55.942 --> 00:20:59.097
charge, so if you put them next
to a million coulombs nothing

00:20:59.097 --> 00:20:59.730
happens.
 

00:20:59.730 --> 00:21:00.900
So some things have plus charge.
 

00:21:00.900 --> 00:21:02.288
Some things have minus charge.
 

00:21:02.288 --> 00:21:09.337
Some things have no charge,
but they're all contained in

00:21:09.337 --> 00:21:12.028
this Coulomb's Law.
 

00:21:12.028 --> 00:21:16.307
Now, again, skipping all the
intermediate discoveries,

00:21:16.307 --> 00:21:21.230
I want to tell you a couple of
things we know about charge.

00:21:21.230 --> 00:21:30.358
First thing is - q is
conserved.

00:21:30.358 --> 00:21:34.506
Conserved is a physics terms
for saying--does not change with

00:21:34.506 --> 00:21:34.990
time.
 

00:21:34.990 --> 00:21:36.674
For example,
when you say energy is

00:21:36.674 --> 00:21:39.069
conserved,
it means particles can come and

00:21:39.069 --> 00:21:41.160
collide and do all kinds of
things,

00:21:41.160 --> 00:21:44.281
but if you add that energy
before, you'll get the same

00:21:44.281 --> 00:21:47.098
answer afterwards,
and whenever that happens,

00:21:47.098 --> 00:21:48.740
the quantity is conserved.
 

00:21:48.740 --> 00:21:52.298
The claim is electrical charge
is conserved.

00:21:52.298 --> 00:21:55.700
So electrical charge may
migrate from A to B or B to A,

00:21:55.700 --> 00:21:57.029
but if you add up the total
charge,

00:21:57.029 --> 00:22:00.250
say the chemical reaction of
any process,

00:22:00.250 --> 00:22:02.913
including in big particle
accelerators where things

00:22:02.913 --> 00:22:05.630
collide and all kinds of stuff
comes flying out,

00:22:05.630 --> 00:22:08.990
the charge of the final
products always equal to the

00:22:08.990 --> 00:22:11.230
charge of the incoming products.
 

00:22:11.230 --> 00:22:16.278
But charge conservation needs
to be amended with one extra

00:22:16.278 --> 00:22:18.759
term, extra qualification.
 

00:22:18.759 --> 00:22:22.278
It's called local.
 

00:22:22.278 --> 00:22:26.327
Suppose I say the number of
students in the class is

00:22:26.327 --> 00:22:27.278
conserved?
 

00:22:27.278 --> 00:22:31.078
That means you count them any
time, you've got to get the same

00:22:31.078 --> 00:22:31.640
number.
 

00:22:31.640 --> 00:22:33.880
Well, here's one possibility.
 

00:22:33.880 --> 00:22:39.589
Suddenly one of you guys
disappears and appears here at

00:22:39.589 --> 00:22:41.598
the same instant.
 

00:22:41.598 --> 00:22:44.611
That's also consistent with
conservation of student number

00:22:44.611 --> 00:22:46.460
because the number didn't
change.

00:22:46.460 --> 00:22:50.348
What disappeared there,
appeared here.

00:22:50.348 --> 00:22:53.174
But that is not a local
conservation of charge because

00:22:53.174 --> 00:22:56.373
it disappears in one part of the
world and appears in another

00:22:56.373 --> 00:22:56.798
one.
 

00:22:56.798 --> 00:23:03.038
And it's not even a meaningful
law to have in the presence of

00:23:03.038 --> 00:23:04.390
relativity.
 

00:23:04.390 --> 00:23:09.808
Can any of you guys think of
why that might be true,

00:23:09.808 --> 00:23:13.568
why a charge disappearing
somewhere and appearing

00:23:13.568 --> 00:23:17.720
somewhere else cannot be a very
profound principle?

00:23:17.720 --> 00:23:18.650
Yes?
 

00:23:18.650 --> 00:23:19.240
Student: 
&gt;

00:23:19.240 --> 00:23:20.980
Prof: Yep?
 

00:23:20.980 --> 00:23:22.799
Student:  Well,
if it's in the same instant

00:23:22.799 --> 00:23:24.844
disappearing from one place and
appearing another place,

00:23:24.844 --> 00:23:26.220
it's traveling faster than
light?

00:23:26.220 --> 00:23:29.503
Prof: Well,
we don't know that it was the

00:23:29.503 --> 00:23:31.740
same thing that even traveled.
 

00:23:31.740 --> 00:23:33.630
It may not have traveled.
 

00:23:33.630 --> 00:23:36.838
It may even be--Here's another
thing.

00:23:36.838 --> 00:23:40.049
Suppose an electron,
suppose a proton disappears

00:23:40.049 --> 00:23:42.509
there and a positron appears
here.

00:23:42.509 --> 00:23:45.661
That still conserves charge,
but we don't think that the

00:23:45.661 --> 00:23:48.470
proton traveled and became the
positron, right?

00:23:48.470 --> 00:23:51.960
So it is not that it has
traveled.

00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:52.390
You are right.
 

00:23:52.390 --> 00:23:53.509
I hadn't thought about that.
 

00:23:53.509 --> 00:23:56.882
It's a good point that it
implies it traveled infinitely

00:23:56.882 --> 00:24:00.009
fast, but that's not the reason
you object to it.

00:24:00.009 --> 00:24:00.808
Yep?
 

00:24:00.808 --> 00:24:03.980
Student:  It's not
necessarily simultaneous.

00:24:03.980 --> 00:24:05.160
Prof: That is the
correct answer.

00:24:05.160 --> 00:24:10.369
The answer is it is not
simultaneous in every frame of

00:24:10.369 --> 00:24:11.548
reference.
 

00:24:11.548 --> 00:24:14.645
You must know from the special
theory that if two events are

00:24:14.645 --> 00:24:16.848
simultaneous in one frame of
reference,

00:24:16.848 --> 00:24:19.598
if you see those same two
events in a moving train,

00:24:19.598 --> 00:24:23.598
or plane, or anything they will
not be simultaneous.

00:24:23.598 --> 00:24:26.288
Therefore, in any other frame
of reference,

00:24:26.288 --> 00:24:29.491
either the charge would have
been created first and then

00:24:29.491 --> 00:24:32.230
after a period of time
reappeared somewhere,

00:24:32.230 --> 00:24:35.529
I mean, destroyed somewhere and
appeared after a delay,

00:24:35.529 --> 00:24:38.558
or the appearance could take
place before the destruction,

00:24:38.558 --> 00:24:41.490
so suddenly you've got two
charges.

00:24:41.490 --> 00:24:48.130
So conservation of charge,
which is conserved non-locally,

00:24:48.130 --> 00:24:50.797
cannot have a significance
except in one frame of

00:24:50.797 --> 00:24:52.862
reference,
but if you believe that all

00:24:52.862 --> 00:24:55.844
observers are equivalent and you
want to write down laws that

00:24:55.844 --> 00:24:58.279
make sense for everybody it can
only be local.

00:24:58.279 --> 00:25:01.914
So electrical charge is
conserved and it is local,

00:25:01.914 --> 00:25:03.400
locally conserved.
 

00:25:03.400 --> 00:25:05.329
In other words,
stuff doesn't just disappear.

00:25:05.329 --> 00:25:07.210
Stuff just moves around.
 

00:25:07.210 --> 00:25:10.681
You can keep track of it,
and if you add it up you get

00:25:10.681 --> 00:25:11.858
the same number.
 

00:25:11.858 --> 00:25:19.740
The second part of q,
which is not necessary for any

00:25:19.740 --> 00:25:27.618
of these older phenomena,
is that q is quantized.

00:25:27.618 --> 00:25:32.971
That means the electrical
charge that we run into does not

00:25:32.971 --> 00:25:36.538
take a continuum of possible
values.

00:25:36.538 --> 00:25:38.279
For example,
the length of any object,

00:25:38.279 --> 00:25:40.490
you might think at least in
classical mechanics,

00:25:40.490 --> 00:25:41.759
is any number you like.
 

00:25:41.759 --> 00:25:45.549
It's a continuous variable,
but electric charge is not

00:25:45.549 --> 00:25:46.480
continuous.
 

00:25:46.480 --> 00:25:50.189
As far as we can tell,
all the charges we have ever

00:25:50.189 --> 00:25:54.640
seen are all multiples of a
certain basic unit of charge,

00:25:54.640 --> 00:26:04.048
which turns out to be 1.6 times
10 to the -19 coulombs.

00:26:04.048 --> 00:26:07.028
Every charge is either that or
some multiple of it.

00:26:07.028 --> 00:26:11.259
Multiple could be plus or minus
multiple.

00:26:11.259 --> 00:26:16.650
So charge is granular,
not continuous.

00:26:16.650 --> 00:26:22.067
Okay, so I'm going to give you
a little more knowledge we have

00:26:22.067 --> 00:26:27.041
had since the time of Coulomb
that sort or explains these

00:26:27.041 --> 00:26:28.019
things.
 

00:26:28.019 --> 00:26:31.200
I mean, what's really going on
microscopically?

00:26:31.200 --> 00:26:32.950
We don't have to pretend we
don't know.

00:26:32.950 --> 00:26:37.598
We do, so we might as well use
that information from now on.

00:26:37.598 --> 00:26:42.040
What we do know is that
everything is made up of atoms,

00:26:42.040 --> 00:26:46.400
and that if you look into the
atom it's got a nucleus,

00:26:46.400 --> 00:26:48.950
a lot of guys sitting here.
 

00:26:48.950 --> 00:26:53.440
Some are called protons and
some are called neutrons,

00:26:53.440 --> 00:26:58.880
and then there are some guys
running around called electrons.

00:26:58.880 --> 00:27:02.903
Of course we will see at the
end of the semester that this

00:27:02.903 --> 00:27:06.221
picture is wrong,
but it is good enough for this

00:27:06.221 --> 00:27:07.068
purpose.
 

00:27:07.068 --> 00:27:11.316
It's certainly true that there
are charges in an atom which are

00:27:11.316 --> 00:27:15.220
near the center and other light
charges which are near the

00:27:15.220 --> 00:27:17.068
periphery, are outside.
 

00:27:17.068 --> 00:27:21.019
All things carrying electric
charge in our world in daily

00:27:21.019 --> 00:27:23.769
life are either protons or
electrons.

00:27:23.769 --> 00:27:26.910
