00:34:20.619 --> 00:34:25.079
find the force due to
q_3 and you add

00:34:25.079 --> 00:34:26.090
them up.
 

00:34:26.090 --> 00:34:34.139
The fact that you can add these
two vectors is not a logical

00:34:34.139 --> 00:34:36.050
requirement.
 

00:34:36.050 --> 00:34:39.800
In fact, it's not even true at
an extremely accurate level that

00:34:39.800 --> 00:34:43.612
the force between two charges is
not affected by the presence of

00:34:43.612 --> 00:34:44.579
a third one.
 

00:34:44.579 --> 00:34:46.168
But it's an excellent
approximation,

00:34:46.168 --> 00:34:48.753
but you must realize it is
something you've got to find to

00:34:48.753 --> 00:34:49.980
be true experimentally.
 

00:34:49.980 --> 00:34:53.820
It's not something you can say
is logical consequence.

00:34:53.820 --> 00:34:57.577
Logically there is no reason
why the interaction between two

00:34:57.577 --> 00:35:01.719
entities should not be affected
by the presence of a third one.

00:35:01.719 --> 00:35:05.929
But it seems to be a very good
approximation for what we do,

00:35:05.929 --> 00:35:08.911
and that's the reason why
eventually we can find the force

00:35:08.911 --> 00:35:12.121
between an extended object,
another extended object by

00:35:12.121 --> 00:35:15.846
looking at the force on everyone
of these due to everyone of

00:35:15.846 --> 00:35:18.119
those and adding all the
vectors.

00:35:18.119 --> 00:35:21.739
Okay, so superposition plus
Coulomb's Law is what you need.

00:35:21.739 --> 00:35:24.989
Then you can certainly
understand the attraction.

00:35:24.989 --> 00:35:29.639
How about the comb and the
