00:36:03.869 --> 00:36:07.530
near these positive charges from
the other end,

00:36:07.530 --> 00:36:11.050
leaving positive charges in the
back,

00:36:11.050 --> 00:36:13.643
so that the system will
separate into a little bit of

00:36:13.643 --> 00:36:17.827
negative closer to the positive,
and the leftover positive will

00:36:17.827 --> 00:36:19.210
be further away.
 

00:36:19.210 --> 00:36:22.911
Therefore, even though it's
neutral the attraction of plus

00:36:22.911 --> 00:36:26.940
for this minus is stronger than
the repulsion of this plus with

00:36:26.940 --> 00:36:27.849
this plus.
 

00:36:27.849 --> 00:36:29.380
That's called polarization.
 

00:36:29.380 --> 00:36:32.510
So polarization is when charge
separates.

00:36:32.510 --> 00:36:34.706
Some materials cannot be
polarized, in which case no

00:36:34.706 --> 00:36:37.119
matter how much you do this with
a comb it won't work.

00:36:37.119 --> 00:36:39.090
Some materials can be polarized.
 

00:36:39.090 --> 00:36:42.507
The piece of paper is an
example of what can be

00:36:42.507 --> 00:36:43.400
polarized.
 

00:36:43.400 --> 00:36:44.960
We can understand that too.
 

00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:47.748
And in this example,
if you bring a lot of plus

00:36:47.748 --> 00:36:50.367
charges here,
and you look at what's going on

00:36:50.367 --> 00:36:52.617
here,
the minus guys here will sit

00:36:52.617 --> 00:36:55.969
here and the plus will be left
over in the back,

00:36:55.969 --> 00:36:59.045
and then this attraction
between plus and minus is bigger

00:36:59.045 --> 00:37:02.880
than this repulsion,
so it will be attracted to it.

00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:06.155
But once it touches it,
this rod touches that,

00:37:06.155 --> 00:37:09.869
then what you have is a lot of
